<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently the Zend_Cache::factory method does not accept Zend_Config as an object.</p>

<p>I would suggest that, calling the function with just one parameter which is instance of Zend_Config does search for a valid config with the keys:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$config-&gt;frontend;
$config-&gt;backend;
$config-&gt;frontendOptions;
$config-&gt;backendOptions;
</code></pre>

<p>This would greatly enhance the use of the factory.</p>

    </div>
</div>

